---
/*
 * S03DesignPhilosophy.astro — Design Philosophy section
 *
 * Palette-break mode: parchment ground, copper eyebrow, Lora h2.
 * This is the first "exhale" moment — the dark field gives way to warm cream.
 * iyo-clean two-zone pattern via Section.astro's entry/content slots.
 *
 * Entry slot (min-height: 100vh, ~85% negative space):
 *   Eyebrow (conceptual/copper) → BlurReveal(h2) → lead paragraph
 *
 * Default slot (body below the entry viewport):
 *   3 principle blocks (with hairline dividers) → "Why mechanism…" sub-section → UpNextTeaser
 *
 * PARCHMENT RULE: All text uses --text-on-break (#1A1815). Section.astro sets
 * `color: var(--text-on-break)` on .section--parchment which cascades to all
 * descendants. h1/h2/h3 are additionally overridden by Section.astro's
 * .section__entry--parchment and .section__content--parchment rules.
 *
 * Use rgba(26,24,21,x) for reduced-opacity text to avoid opacity-cascade
 * issues that would otherwise affect nested strong/em elements.
 *
 * Content sourced from: .design/sections/03-design-philosophy.md
 */
import Section from '../components/sections/Section.astro';
import Eyebrow from '../components/content/Eyebrow.astro';
import BlurReveal from '../components/content/BlurReveal.astro';
import UpNextTeaser from '../components/content/UpNextTeaser.astro';
---

<Section id="s3" label="Design Philosophy" background="parchment">

  <Fragment slot="entry">
    <div class="s03-entry">
      <Eyebrow label="DESIGN PHILOSOPHY" mode="conceptual" />
      <BlurReveal>
        <h2 class="s03-entry__headline">
          Three ideas shape how Amplifier is built.
        </h2>
      </BlurReveal>
      <p class="s03-entry__lead">
        They weren't written on a whiteboard first. They emerged from the code, from decisions made repeatedly about what belongs in the kernel and what doesn't.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Fragment>

  <!--
    .s03-content wrapper enables scoped :global overrides for UpNextTeaser's
    dark-mode defaults (--text-primary white, rgba(255,255,255) borders)
    which need to be inverted on the parchment background.
  -->
  <div class="s03-content">

    <div class="s03-blocks">

      <div class="s03-block">
        <p class="s03-block__text">
          <strong class="s03-block__name">Mechanism, not policy.</strong>
          The kernel fires a tool:pre event before every tool call. A safety module decides whether to block it. A logging module records it. The kernel has no opinion about what should happen. It fires events and collects results. This separation has a name: mechanism versus policy.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="s03-block">
        <p class="s03-block__text">
          <strong class="s03-block__name">The center stays still.</strong>
          A new AI model ships. Someone writes a provider module. The kernel does not know or care which model it talks to. New tools, new paradigms, new safety requirements: all handled at the edges. The center does not move.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="s03-block">
        <p class="s03-block__text">
          <strong class="s03-block__name">Ruthless simplicity.</strong>
          Search the entire amplifier-core codebase for file-writing operations: zero matches. The kernel does not write logs, save transcripts, or persist configuration. If something can live in a module, it must.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="s03-why">
      <h3 class="s03-why__heading">Why mechanism over policy matters in practice</h3>

      <p class="s03-why__text">
        Consider what happens when you deploy an AI agent in a setting where certain operations need human approval. In a system without this separation, you would modify the tool-calling code itself: add an if-statement, check a config flag, pop up a dialog. The approval logic is now woven into the execution logic. Every future tool must remember to include the approval check. Miss one, and the policy has a hole.
      </p>

      <p class="s03-why__text">
        In Amplifier, the kernel fires a tool:pre event before every tool call. A hook module registers for that event. When it sees a tool call that requires approval, it returns ask_user. The kernel pauses execution and waits for a human decision. The tool itself has no knowledge that approval was required. The hook module can be swapped, updated, or removed without touching any tool code. The policy lives in a module; the mechanism lives in the kernel.
      </p>

      <p class="s03-why__text">
        This pattern repeats at every level. Logging is a hook, not a kernel feature. Context injection is a hook response, not an API call. Safety rules are hook policies, not built-in constraints. Each policy can be independently developed, tested, and replaced.
      </p>
    </div>

    <UpNextTeaser
      nextSection="The Kernel"
      teaser="Five things live in the kernel. Nothing else."
    />

  </div>

</Section>

<style>
  /* ── Entry cluster ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
   * Parchment conceptual entry: copper eyebrow (mode="conceptual" handles),
   * Lora h2 in --text-on-break ink, Inter lead at reduced opacity.
   * ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .s03-entry {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .s03-entry :global(.blur-reveal) {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3); /* 24px: headline → lead */
  }

  .s03-entry__headline {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: var(--text-h2);             /* clamp(1.5rem, 2.5vw, 2.25rem) */
    font-weight: 600;
    line-height: var(--leading-tight);     /* 1.15 */
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-tight); /* -0.02em */
    color: var(--text-on-break);           /* #1A1815 ink on parchment */
    max-width: 24ch;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .s03-entry__lead {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: clamp(1.125rem, 1.2vw, 1.25rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);   /* 1.8 — conceptual breathing room */
    /* Use rgba directly to avoid opacity-cascade onto BlurReveal chars */
    color: rgba(26, 24, 21, 0.75);         /* --text-on-break at 75% */
    max-width: 55ch;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ── Principle blocks ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
   * 3 philosophy principles, each separated by a hairline divider.
   * Body text at 80% opacity for reading weight; principle names at full.
   * Uses rgba() not opacity so strong inherits full color, not stacked opacity.
   * ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .s03-blocks {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    max-width: 60ch;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--divider-on-break); /* rgba(26,24,21,0.12) */
  }

  .s03-block {
    padding: var(--space-5) 0;             /* 40px top/bottom per principle */
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--divider-on-break);
  }

  .s03-block__text {
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);   /* 1.8 — conceptual section */
    /* 80% opacity body text; avoids opacity cascade by using rgba() */
    color: rgba(26, 24, 21, 0.8);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* Principle name (bold prefix) — full ink weight */
  .s03-block__name {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-on-break);           /* #1A1815 — full opacity */
  }

  /* ── "Why mechanism…" sub-section ───────────────────────────────────────────
   * Three explanatory paragraphs after the principle blocks.
   * Heading uses Lora for conceptual weight; paragraphs match block styling.
   * ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .s03-why {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-3);                   /* 24px between paragraphs */
    max-width: 60ch;
    margin-top: var(--space-8);            /* visual separation from blocks */
  }

  .s03-why__heading {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: var(--text-h3);             /* clamp(1.125rem, 1.5vw, 1.5rem) */
    font-weight: 600;
    line-height: var(--leading-tight);
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-tight);
    color: var(--text-on-break);           /* #1A1815 */
    margin: 0;
  }

  .s03-why__text {
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);   /* 1.8 */
    color: rgba(26, 24, 21, 0.8);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ── UpNextTeaser: parchment overrides ──────────────────────────────────────
   * UpNextTeaser uses dark-mode defaults: --text-primary (white), white
   * glass borders, white divider. All need inversion on parchment.
   * Scoped via .s03-content so overrides don't bleed to other sections.
   * ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */

  /* Hairline separator above the teaser */
  .s03-content :global(.up-next) {
    border-top-color: var(--divider-on-break);
  }

  /* Glass container: invert from white-alpha to black-alpha */
  .s03-content :global(.up-next__glass) {
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.03);
    border-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
  }

  /* "Up next" micro-label */
  .s03-content :global(.up-next__label) {
    color: rgba(26, 24, 21, 0.55);
  }

  /* Section name (was --text-primary = white; needs ink) */
  .s03-content :global(.up-next__section) {
    color: var(--text-on-break);
  }

  /* Teaser tagline */
  .s03-content :global(.up-next__teaser) {
    color: rgba(26, 24, 21, 0.65);
  }
</style>
